releases.body:
 Migrates text search data from an old table to a new table with optional encryption.
 Used for migrating un-encrypted search terms to encrypted storage.
 Document ID mappings are preserved (both internal and external IDs stay the same).

 Usage example:
 using (var tran = engine.GetTransaction())
 {
     tran.SynchronizeTables("OldTable", "NewTable");
     var encryptor = new DBreeze.TextSearch.WabiStreamCrypto(key, iv);
     tran.Support_Migration_TextSearchMigrateTable("OldTable", "NewTable", encryptor);
     tran.Commit();
 }
 engine.Scheme.DeleteTable("OldTable");
 engine.Scheme.RenameTable("OldTable", "NewTable");
